{"author":{"id":"75732e82453cc4795a3b5d7bef7a9ce916b428e5bbe06161843f7392657be5c1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1444308471,"nonce":"0mOY7M94OPqkiD74QjmdItJUKCs=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0NjUyNzgzMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/304#issuecomment-146527832"},"message":"Oh yeah I didn't mention everything. R doesn't support and compile with X11 which is logical, because it should work on machines that have no X installed too. If I remember correctly, the problem didn't occur on Desktop machines, but only on machines without X11. When I tried to solve it, I thought the anwers was by using cairo libraries to do the drawing rather than X11, but I never got that far so I should not make the decision.\n\nI was thinking of the following solution because it recreates the diff file and is line number based  (didn't actually test it...):\n\n```\ntouch configure_patch.diff\n\necho '--- mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14.orig/build/configure.ac.warnings' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '+++ mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14/build/configure.ac.warnings' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '@@ -39,7 +39,7 @@ dnl options. Namely, the following:' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho 'dnl -flto working really needs a test link, not just a compile' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho 'safe_MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN\"\\' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '-MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto\"' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '+MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto -ffat-lto-objects -fuse-linker-plugin\"' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho 'AC_TRY_LINK([],' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho 'int main(int argc, char **argv) { return 0; }' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho ',[],[' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '--- mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14.orig/configure' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '+++ mingw64-x-cairo-1.12.14/configure' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '@@ -18162,7 +18162,7 @@ MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -erroff=E_ENUM_T' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho 'safe_MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN\"' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '-MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto\"' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '+MAYBE_WARN=\"$MAYBE_WARN -flto -ffat-lto-objects -fuse-linker-plugin\"' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho 'cat confdefs.h - \u003c\u003c_ACEOF \u003econftest.$ac_ext' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\necho '/ end confdefs.h. /' \u003e\u003e configure_patch.diff\n\npatch configure_patch.diff\n```\n\nBut whatever is more comfortable to you!","files":null}]}